25/05/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Romanian President Traian Basescu asked political parties Friday (May 23rd) during the opening of a social and economic forum to act responsibly on economic policy so that Romania could adopt the euro in 2014. Among areas requiring improvement, he cited productivity, energy efficiency, legal transparency, security of pensions and aid for vulnerable citizens. Basescu also advised officials to upgrade the public administration system to attract more European Commission support and to modernize railroads to encourage investment in all sectors. (Hotnews.ro - 24/05/08; Rompres - 23/05/08)
